caption: “The common man will find no peace until the last politician is strangled on the entrails of the last priest” Denis Diderot

One of the greatest representatives of the French Enlightenment (Langres 1713 - Paris 1784). Son of a craftsman, he did his first studies in a Jesuit college and was briefly initiated into the ecclesiastical state; he moved to Paris, where he obtained the title of maître ès arts (1732).

I like this statue enthroned in the center of Place Jacques Copeau, facing Boulevard Saint-Germain. Its location is good. I think the sculptor thought out the position of the body well. As we get closer, we see lots of very interesting details. Unfortunately, pigeons like to land on its head and leave souvenirs: it deserves to be cleaned regularly.
Neighborhood where it is good to stroll while enjoying the highlights of the 5th and 6th arrondissements.
The statue of the writer and philosopher Denis Diderot (1713-1784), made by Jean Gautherin (1840-1890), is located opposite 145 Boulevard Saint Germain

Statue of the French writer and philosopher which is located behind a bus stop. Diderot is particularly known for having directed the writing of the encyclopedia with the assistance of numerous authors. He was born in Langres (52) in 1713 and died in 1784 in Paris. A little Karcher wouldn't go amiss.

Beautiful emotion. A walk through the Latin Quarter, alone, without speaking even bad French, at night and... resulted in my first photos that were seen. Diderot frequented the area and the statue is very interesting. Like the one represented.

Very beautiful statue, too bad many people don't know Diderot... For the record this place is on the site of Diderot's former home which was demolished for the construction of the boulevard under Hausmann

When Diderot wrote to his lover, the candle in front of the case was burning down. He was not sure whether the handwriting was clear in the dark, so he wrote, "What you can't understand is that I love you."
Very nice status, unfortunately the pigeons got loose!
